	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I recommend Dark Elf:<br>1) DE have great int as well as good values in other stats.<br>2) DE have a cool and interesting home city, as opposed to the lameass cludge that passes itself off as Felwithe, and the bloddy awful city of Kelethin with all those annoying goody-goody woodelf treehugging types.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>3) DE get the HIDE skill.  I cannot eludidate to you enough that this skill alone makes a DE caster superior to all others.  this is because critters attack casters by choice, and especially those casters who are sitting down.  since you wont get invis untill level 16, and it doesnt work while medding anyways, you will always be finding yourself insta-blicked by anything that drops out of the sky.<br>4) DE get nightvision like High Elves, but are better drawn.  High elves look like they havent been worked on since before the beta, and it shows.<br>5) DE Look Cool<br>6) Make money by smuggling objects that others desperately need from Neriak.<br>7) DE stick together.<br>8) Not having to put up with pratting NPCs who issue forth vomitously saccharine dialogue.<br>9) You get to pick on high elves, talk about your best Hairfoot Stew Recipe and hunt the Halflings in the forest of Nek!<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
